Le triangle $A'B'C'$ est l'image de $ABC$ par la symétrie d'axe $(d)$. Donner les coordonnées des points $A'$, $B'$ et $C'$.  egin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.6] \draw[step=1cm,gray!50,very thin] (-4.5,-0.5) grid (4.5,4.5); \draw[->, thick] (-4.5,0) -- (4.5,0) node[below] {$x$}; \draw[->, thick] (0,-0.5) -- (0,4.5) node[left] {$y$}; \draw[black, very thick] (0, -0.5) -- (0, 4.5) node[right] {$(d)$}; \draw [line width=1.pt, fill=black, opacity=0.3] (1,1) -- (3,1) -- (1,3) -- cycle; 
ode[black, below] at (1,1) {A}; 
ode[black, below] at (3,1) {B}; 
ode[black, above] at (1,3) {C}; \end{tikzpicture}

